  \## How to use Swagger?

%section{"data-markdown" => ""}
  \#### New API: Top-Down
  * Use the Swagger **Editor** to create your Swagger definition
  * Use the Swagger **Codegen** tools to generate server implementation

%section{"data-markdown" => ""}
  \#### Existing API: Bottom-Up
  * You have an existing REST API
  * You want to create a Swagger definition
  * Option A: Create the definition manually using the Swagger Editor
  * Option B: Integrate the framework into your Code and get the Swagger definition generated automatically

%section{"data-markdown" => ""}
  \#### Build a new client for a Swagger-described API
  * Use the online version of the Swagger UI to explore the API
  * (given that you have a URL to the APIs Swagger definition)
  * Use Swagger Codegen to generate the client library

